<font color="#FF0000">SOCKS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct 23 14:56:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
I remember seven open sores on the bottom of my feet.  Randy McCall (medic) sent me back to base camp to dry them out for a few days.  Extra dry socks didn't stay dry for long.<br><br>
The water in the rice paddies was warm in the late afternoon.   The water was cool in the morning.  I can still sense the rice paddy water slowly seeping in through the two vents in the side of my jungle boots.<br><br>
I was &quot;tempted&quot; to take my boots off at night on perimeter duty, but couldn't do it.  The idea that Charlie would catch me with my boots off didn't cut it.<br><br>
I think we had one or two guys in the platoon that &quot;lived&quot; without wearing socks.  They were HARDCORE.  I tried that once -- my feet weren't tough enough.<br><br>
Paul
